NAME
	tk-gallery (tk-display) - render one of every core Tk widget class twice, engine defaults beside a flat and padded treatment, as a toolkit review instrument

INTERFACE
	tk-display (MatrixTkDisplay)

READS
	nothing (the mount argument is unused; pass /)

WRITES
	nothing

DESCRIPTION
	A review instrument for the toolkit's look, not a data view.  One
	shared grid, one widget class per row, so the two treatments
	align row for row: column 0 renders button, checkbutton,
	radiobutton, choicebutton, menubutton (with menu), label, entry,
	listbox, scale, scrollbar, canvas, and text exactly as the
	engine's defaults draw them (raised/sunken bevels, text-tight
	targets); column 1 renders the same widgets in the proposed
	InferNode treatment: -relief flat -borderwidth 1 (2D, no bevels)
	and grid -ipadx/-ipady on interactive widgets — internal padding
	that grows the widget's actual hit target, per the 44pt/48dp
	minimum-touch-target conventions.  The grid lives on a frame
	hosted as a canvas window item with a scrollbar driving yview, so
	the gallery fits any region height.

	Widgets carry representative content (entry text, list items, a
	set scale, drawn canvas items) so insets and bevels are visible
	in use.  Compare the columns, then decide the default treatment;
	per-widget options cover everything shown, and anything chosen as
	a DEFAULT belongs in the Tk engine (libtk) rather than in every
	module.  Engine limits the gallery makes visible: no "solid"
	relief (a flat button has no outline), radiobutton indicators
	identical to checkbuttons, top-anchored text in tall widgets, a
	hardcoded sunken bevel on press.

SEE ALSO
	video-ctl (a Tk control surface using padded targets)
	libtk/buton.c (relief and border defaults), libtk/xdata.c
	(generic -relief/-borderwidth options, supported relief values)
